com.nokia.places

Interface PlaceLink

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ApiLink, Item

    public interface PlaceLink
extends Item
    Represents a link containing discovery information about a Place.
    See Also:
    Nokia's Restful Places API - Results

    • Method Detail

      • getPosition

        GeoCoordinate getPosition()
        This method retrieves the geographical position of the place.
        Returns:
        The GeoCoordinate for the place.

      • getDistance

        java.lang.Integer getDistance()
        This method retrieves the distance to the place.

        Note: Distance information for a place is optional. A call to this method could return null.

        Returns:
        The distance to the place (could be null).

      • getAverageRating

        java.lang.Double getAverageRating()
        This method retrieves the average rating for a place.

        Note: The average rating is set to zero for places with no ratings.

        Returns:
        The average rating for the place.

      • getCategory

        Category getCategory()
        This method retrieves the link to the primary category of the place.
        Returns:
        The Category to the primary category of the place.

      • getVicinity

        RichText getVicinity()
        This method retrieves the textual description of the location of the place, of its vicinity. This is usually derived from the address, but could also contain any other description that helps a user understand where the place is located.
        Returns:
        The RichText description of the vicinity for the place.

      • getBoundingBox

        GeoBoundingBox getBoundingBox()
        This method retrieves the enclosing bounding box that describes a range of coordinates corresponding to the location of the place. Typically, bounding boxes are associated with places such as cities and countries.

        Note: Bounding box information for a place is optional. A call to this method could return null.

        Returns:
        The GeoBoundingBox containing the place (could be null).

      • getSponsored

        java.lang.Boolean getSponsored()
        This method indicates whether this search result is sponsored. Applications must provide some visual differentiation between sponsored search results and regular search results.

        Note: Sponsorship is an optional attribute for a place.

        Returns:
        true if the search result is sponsored, false for regular searches.

      • getHaving

        java.lang.String[] getHaving()
        This method retrieves data associated with the Having attribute.
        Returns:
        Data associated with the Having attribute.
